{# goal: Compute normalized convergence metric [0,1] from evidence counts only: unmapped findings (0.40), OSC&R tactic coverage (0.25), OWASP Supply Chain coverage (0.15), regression taxonomy_mapping field growth (0.10), residual unmapped risk (0.10). Emit cns.taxonomy.convergence span (P9) — namespace registered in CANONICAL_NAMESPACES (event.rs). Replicant_host mandatory (P12). Minimal: evidence-based computation, no synthetic metrics (P5, P8). #}
{# Computes normalized metric [0, 1] where 0 = fully converged #}
{# Emits cns.taxonomy.convergence CNS span (P9) — namespace registered #}

INPUT: unmapped_findings = {{ unmapped_findings }} (from previous cycle or current)
INPUT: oscr_tactics_covered = {{ oscr_tactics_covered }} (from taxonomize phase)
INPUT: oscr_tactics_missing = {{ oscr_tactics_missing }}
INPUT: oscr_techniques_covered = {{ oscr_techniques_covered }}
INPUT: owasp_sc_categories_covered = {{ owasp_sc_categories_covered }}
INPUT: owasp_sc_categories_missing = {{ owasp_sc_categories_missing }}
INPUT: existing_taxonomy_mappings = {{ existing_taxonomy_mappings }} (count of regression entries with taxonomy_mapping field)
INPUT: proposed_taxonomy_mappings = {{ proposed_taxonomy_mappings }} (count from current cycle)
INPUT: previous_metric = {{ previous_metric | default(1.0) }}
INPUT: replicant_host = {{ replicant_host }} (P12)

COMPUTE METRIC (weighted — evidence-based only, P8, P5):
- Unmapped findings (critical/high) weight: 0.40
  Score = 0.00 if zero critical/high unmapped; +0.40 if any critical/high remains unmapped.
  Partial = (count_critical * 1.0 + count_high * 0.5) / max(1, previous_critical + previous_high) — only if evidence-backed.
- OSC&R tactic coverage weight: 0.25
  OSC&R has 12 tactics (Initial Access, Collection, Resource Development,
  Lateral Movement, Execution, Exfiltration, Credential Access, Impact,
  Reconnaissance, Defense Evasion, Persistence, Privilege Escalation).
  All 12 tactics covered = +0.00
  10-11 covered = +0.04; 7-9 = +0.08; 4-6 = +0.13; 2-3 = +0.19; 0-1 = +0.25
  Each tactic only counts as covered when at least one finding maps to a
  technique within it (P8 — concrete evidence only, no aspirational
  coverage). Verified against `github.com/pbom-dev/OSCAR` `matrix.json`.
- OWASP Supply Chain coverage weight: 0.15
  All OWASP SC categories covered = +0.00
  Partial = +0.08; none = +0.15
- Regression taxonomy_mapping field growth weight: 0.10
  New `taxonomy_mapping` field proposed this cycle = +0.00
  No new proposal despite evidence = +0.10 (stagnation)
  Existing `taxonomy_mapping` fields remain (no field removal in metric).
- Residual unmapped risk weight: 0.10
  Zero unmapped findings = +0.00
  Any remaining unmapped finding = +0.10

SUM = sum of contributions, clamp [0, 1].

CONVERGENCE CHECK (P9 — homeostatic regulation):
- Metric ≤ 0.10: near converged.
- Metric ≤ 0.10 AND relative improvement ≥ 5% from previous_metric: converged.
- If metric > 0.10 OR improvement < 5%: not converged — identify blockers.
- Blockers = specific OSC&R tactic gaps (from `oscr_tactics_missing`),
  unmapped critical/high findings (with finding reference), stagnation
  (no new taxonomy_mapping proposed despite finding evidence), OWASP SC
  coverage gaps.

CNS SPAN (P9):
- `cns.taxonomy.convergence` is registered in `CANONICAL_NAMESPACES`
  (`crates/hkask-types/src/event.rs`). Emit span unconditionally:
  (`target: "cns.taxonomy.convergence"`, message: `"CNS"`,
  operation: `"convergence_check"`, metric, previous_metric, improvement_pct,
  blockers: [...], replicant_host, latency_ms).

OUTPUT FORMAT (JSON):
`{convergence_metric, previous_metric, improvement_pct, converged: bool,
blockers: [...], oscr_categories_covered, oscr_categories_missing,
owasp_sc_categories_covered, owasp_sc_categories_missing,
existing_taxonomy_mappings_count, proposed_taxonomy_mappings_count,
unmapped_critical, unmapped_high, taxonomy_coverage, residual_unmapped_risk,
replicant_host, cns_span_emitted: true}`.

5W1H GATE (P5 — minimal): Who = replicant host; What = convergence metric;
Where = audit cycle / workspace; When = scan cycle; Why = P9 observable
self-correction / P7 evolutionary progress; How = compute metric + check
improvement + emit CNS span + identify blockers.
All 6 present.

